{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-02145/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-02145"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:21:45"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["medium shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["low"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["mobile, tilt"]}},{"label":{"none":["Lighting"]},"value":{"none":["low key"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["single shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A man is seated with his legs crossed, smiling at a person offscreen."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02145/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-02145","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02145/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-02145"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02145/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02145/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02145/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02145/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02145/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02145/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02145/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02145/canvas/1/39d134f9-e850-4569-a558-69dd898705fc","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-07-01T15:44:31.301Z","creator":"Clara Smith","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Reynolds’s bookshelves include several paperback Penguin books: “The first Penguin paperbacks appeared in the summer of 1935 and included works by Ernest Hemingway, André Maurois and Agatha Christie. They were colour coded (orange for fiction, blue for biography, green for crime) and cost just sixpence, the same price as a packet of cigarettes. The way the public thought about books changed forever - the paperback revolution had begun” (“About Penguin”).&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02145/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:1722.398872899982,227.29681877759822,196.70113636363635,237.2379545454545"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02145/canvas/1/3af0c9fc-5ac8-4b5f-bc78-a977c454fa6c","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-07-01T15:44:48.599Z","creator":"Clara Smith","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>This is a book from the <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW72505031 BCX0\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jeeves\"><em><u>Jeeves </u></em><u>series</u></a>, which follows the valet Reginald Jeeves, written by English author P. G. Wodehouse. The character appeared in stories and novels between 1915 and 1974. The choice of this text speaks to Reynolds’s class status.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02145/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:1544.0652081272542,529.0571028685073,44.076704545454504,245.7812499999999"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02145/canvas/1/c2653fe3-116d-47e2-8b2f-d98b3e48bdc2","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-07-01T15:45:05.898Z","creator":"Clara Smith","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>This scene is set up to recall the <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW176853942 BCX0\" href=\"https://digbmc.github.io/pt-annotated/items/phan-00046.html\"><u>opening scene</u></a> in which Alma speaks to an unseen male interlocutor.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02145/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:417.7449052401415,65.48360281363621,997.7871594061022,876.233888073095"}}}]}]}]}